article_title: Why Obamacare Co-Ops Are Failing At A Rate Of Nearly 50%

article_metadata.author: The Apothecary

og.description: BY ED HAISLMAIER - The bottom line: Obamacare has made health insurance costlier and the business of offering it riskier. To survive in that new world, health insurers need to be cautious, or even pessimistic, and hope that their customers can continue to pay escalating premiums. It’s not a pretty picture.
